# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok some of the nation 's largest banks _ including first union and nationsbank _ are based here , solidifying north carolina 's reputation as the banking state .
# ::alignments
(b / base-01
      :ARG1 (b2 / bank
            :quant (s / some)
            :ARG1-of (ii / include-91
                  :ARG2 (b3 / bank
                        :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                              :ARG2 (l / large)
                              :ARG3 (m / most)
                              :ARG5 (n / nation))
                        :ARG2-of ii
                        :ARG1 (a / and
                              :op1 (b4 / bank
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Union"))
                              :op2 (b5 / bank
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Nationbank"))))))
      :location (h2 / here)
      :ARG0-of (s2 / solidify-01
            :ARG1 (r / repute-01
                  :ARG1 (s3 / state
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "North"
                              :op2 "Carolina"))
                  :ARG2 (b6 / bank))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok economic growth in new york state continued to stagnate last month as the unemployment rate rose again , labor department officials said friday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (g / government-organization
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Labor"
                              :op2 "Department"))
                  :ARG2 (o / official)))
      :ARG1 (c / continue-01
            :ARG1 (s2 / stagnate-01
                  :ARG1 (g2 / grow-01
                        :ARG1 (e / economy)
                        :location (s3 / state
                              :ARG1-of (n2 / new-01)
                              :location (c2 / country
                                    :name n
                                    :op1 "New"
                                    :op2 "York")))))
      :time (m / month
            :mod (l / last))
      :ARG1-of (c3 / cause-01
            :ARG0 (r / rise-01
                  :ARG1 (r2 / rate-01
                        :ARG1 (e2 / employ-01
                              :polarity -))
                  :mod (a / again)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday)))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG0 (c / company
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Pacificorp")

                  :ARG1 (u / utility)))
      :ARG1 (l / launch-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (b / bid-06
                  :ARG1-of (a / agree-01)
                  :ARG0-of (v / value-01
                        :ARG1 (g / group
                              :mod (e / energy)
                              :poss (c2 / country
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Great"
                                          :op2 "Britain")))
                        :ARG2 (m / monetary-quantity
                              :quant 1000000000
                              :unit (p / pound)))
                  :ARG1-of (n3 / new-01)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t / tuesday)))

                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1 p
                  :ARG3 (c / charge-05
                        :ARG1 p
                        :ARG2 (p3 / plunder-01)
                        :mod (c2 / capital))))
      :op3 (t2 / tell-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (f / frame-06
                  :ARG1 p)
            :ARG2 (c3 / court
                  :ARG0-of (o / oppose-01
                        :ARG1 (g / graft-01)))
            :manner (d3 / defiant))

      :time (w / wednesday))

                                                      :mod (e4 / electronics))))))

            :weekday (m2 / monday)))

                  :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                        :value 1)))
